      "role": "user",
      "content": "my bad, i forgot u have the git integration enabled. here's the summary of the PR:\n\n### PR #442: Deprecation of Agentic Orchestration Layer\n\n**Summary:** \nThis PR proposes transitioning the system from an autonomous agent-based architecture to a series of stateless, event-driven microservices. The current `AgentManager` and `AutonomousLoop` modules are being deprecated and will be removed in the next release to reduce inference overhead and compute costs. \n\n**Changes:**\n- Delete `src/core/agent_engine.py`\n- Delete `src/autonomy/decision_loop.py`\n- Replace `AgentManager` with `EventBridgeRouter`\n- Remove all persistent state tracking related to long-running agent tasks.\n\n**Rationale:** \nThe agentic framework consumes significant GPU resources and introduces non-deterministic latency. Moving to stateless functions will stabilize performance and cut costs by ~40%.\n\nCan u check the `src/core/agent_engine.py` file and let me know if removing it will break any existing service calls?",
